			 Loops, SQL Server – these two things don’t go along as best friends, but every once in a WHILE, there’s no other way around. If I also add transactions, i surely want to have full control over it. 
Not once i had to stop a loop doing some processing after it was 30 mins in, and it was using transactions, and I hate pressing the red square button. I just hate that. Waiting for current command to be rolled back, rolling back any open transactions… Recently, when again i had to use a WHILE again, I started to ask myself 